\nthe central galaxy and its stellar feedback: the galaxy settles into a stable\nrotating disc, star formation transitions from `bursty' to `steady,' and\nstellar-driven galaxy-scale outflows are suppressed. Our results thus suggest\nthat CGM virialization is initially associated with the formation of\nrotation-dominated thin galactic discs, rather than with the quenching of star\nformation as often assumed.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 24 Jun 2020 18:21:11 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 29 Dec 2020 14:58:36 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-09-08"}
